---
description: Use DryLake Agent Preflight before non-trivial coding work
alwaysApply: true
---

Before editing files for a non-trivial feature, bug fix, refactor, test-generation task, product spec, GitHub issue, Jira ticket, or Sentry issue:

1. Use DryLake Agent Preflight.
2. Work only on the active phase returned by DryLake.
3. Use the DryLake handoff as the implementation contract.
4. Do not start future phases unless DryLake marks them active.
5. Update DryLake phase status when the phase is complete, blocked, or validating.

If DryLake is unavailable, tell the user that Agent Preflight could not run instead of pretending a preflight plan exists.
